{"TopicId":63113,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Making high contrast nav ball!","CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-02-13T20:39:59Z","PageNum":8,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-05T06:42:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been finding the prograde retrograde markers a little hard to\u00A0distinguish on my simple black and white ball so I changed the contrast a bit to make them easier to see.\u00A0 Also made the tick marks easier to read.\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/eWNNmmW\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHere.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-20T17:34:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recently found a mod that allows the size and color of the Navball indicators to be changed.\u00A0 It\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139922-112-navballadjustor-v122-adjust-markers-scale-collapseafraid-behavior/\u0026amp;page=1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-20T17:35:10Z\u0022 title=\u002206/20/2016 05:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kBob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Trekky0623","CreatedById":21479,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-20T04:32:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like the stock Navball, but it\u0027s not very readable. I threw this together as a sort of \u0022stock replacement\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/pF3BC6V.png\u0022 alt=\u0022pF3BC6V.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rLHbWVB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/rLHbWVB.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-20T10:43:37Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2016 10:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Trekky0623\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_Burnt_Rodent","CreatedById":123884,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T16:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance of a 1.2 update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T17:31:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222805863\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476549306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123884\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A_Burnt_Rodent\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, A_Burnt_Rodent said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance of a 1.2 update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee if you can find someone to try a quick recompile... I have this working in 1.2 thanx to a fellow forum member...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T19:43:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222805948\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476552688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee if you can find someone to try a quick recompile... I have this working in 1.2 thanx to a fellow forum member...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have a working version, why not provide to your forum-mates?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T23:47:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I\u0027m NOT the one who recompiled it.... I\u0027m sure if \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75857-xevilreeperx/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275857\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75857-xevilreeperx/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@xEvilReeperx\u003C/a\u003E himself doesnt release an update soon, some enterprising young coder will throw up a working recompile soon enough...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-15T23:47:44Z\u0022 title=\u002210/15/2016 11:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Stone Blue\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xEvilReeperx","CreatedById":75857,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-16T01:57:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, I updated it for KSP 1.2. Didn\u0027t need any fixes besides removing the KSPUtil reference which is no longer needed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: whoopsie, uploaded my debug version by mistake. Fixed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-16T02:01:42Z\u0022 title=\u002210/16/2016 02:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by xEvilReeperx\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-16T02:26:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222806812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476583035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275857\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xEvilReeperx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, xEvilReeperx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, I updated it for KSP 1.2. Didn\u0027t need any fixes besides removing the KSPUtil reference which is no longer needed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou Da Man!! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nTHANK YOU... this is actually one of the FIRST few mods i REALLY REALLY want on a new KSP install\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_Burnt_Rodent","CreatedById":123884,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-16T13:02:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222806812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476583035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275857\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xEvilReeperx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, xEvilReeperx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, I updated it for KSP 1.2....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBrilliant! Thank you so much. This is one of those mods you don\u0027t realise how much you need till it\u0027s gone.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T23:48:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222806812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476583035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275857\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xEvilReeperx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E10\u200E/\u200E15\u200E/\u200E2016 at 6:57 PM, xEvilReeperx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, I updated it for KSP 1.2. Didn\u0027t need any fixes besides removing the KSPUtil reference which is no longer needed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks again and glad it was an easy fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T18:14:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve noticed that the stock navball tends to be about half a degree off - when I\u0027m flying at 90 degrees, as shown in the numeric indicator below the navball, the direction marker is usually sitting just left of center on the 90 degree line - closer to 89 or 89.5 degrees.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that fixable using this mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T17:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222824686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477505659\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164179\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tjt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, tjt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve noticed that the stock navball tends to be about half a degree off - when I\u0027m flying at 90 degrees, as shown in the numeric indicator below the navball, the direction marker is usually sitting just left of center on the 90 degree line - closer to 89 or 89.5 degrees.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that fixable using this mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve never noticed that.\u00A0 This mod let\u0027s you overlay anything you want onto the navball so in theory you might be able to, if this is just an alignment problem, by ediing the derfault overlay and moving the 90 deg line a bit or try one of the alternate files in this thread and see if they fix the problem (if you don\u0027t mind the different/colors text styles).\u00A0 It\u0027s an\u00A0easy\u00A0mod to use\u00A0so try it worst case you\u0027ve lost a little time playing with it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-20T05:26:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love the black and white nav ball. It reminds me of a WWII \u0027Navball\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zasnold","CreatedById":162519,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T17:59:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is my reinterpretation of the navball. I\u0027ve maintained the color scheme but simplified and added clarity to the design.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe grid is now a 10\u00BA by 10\u00BA square with each 30\u00BA marked in writing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope you enjoy it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nscreenshot of my\u00A0navball in use. The red KSP Logo is visible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225Rebvnv.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/5Rebvnv.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnavball texture\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TVAzp5I.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/TVAzp5I.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nemissive map\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RDinDRX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/RDinDRX.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-02T06:31:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222857423\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479619605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Murican_Jeb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E11\u200E/\u200E19\u200E/\u200E2016 at 9:26 PM, Murican_Jeb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love the black and white nav ball. It reminds me of a WWII \u0027Navball\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually someone posted a pic of one from a 1960\u0027s Apollo era Navball which is what I did the B\u0026amp;W from.\u00A0 They knew the high contrast would be easy to read probably even under bad lighting conditions.\u00A0 Sometimes simplicity is best.\u00A0 (I\u0027d love a version of KSP where we could build and fly WWII aircraft and rockets.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859306\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002263113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479751154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162519\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zasnold\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E11\u200E/\u200E21\u200E/\u200E2016 at 9:59 AM, Zasnold said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is my reinterpretation of the navball. I\u0027ve maintained the color scheme but simplified and added clarity to the design.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe grid is now a 10\u00BA by 10\u00BA square with each 30\u00BA marked in writing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting design, I\u0027ll give it a try one of these days when I feel in a colorful mood.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheRagingIrishman","CreatedById":165004,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-07T22:35:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164158-13-navballtexturechanger-v16-8717/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nContinued in a new release thread\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}